node.title: Armed police swarm Auckland suburb
node.description: Police have been in the area since around 3pm.
node.content: ["Armed police have swarmed an Auckland suburb on Tuesday afternoon after concerns for a person's safety.\u00a0", "Police blocked off Evans Road in Glen Eden around 3:30pm with residents stopped from going into their homes.\u00a0", "Seven vehicles descended on the area at the Captain Scott Rd end with officers also stationed further up Evans Rd.", "\"This afternoon police received a report relating to concerns for a person's safety at an address on Evans Road in Glen Eden,\" a\u00a0 police spokesperson said.\n", "\"Police attended and entered the address where a person was located along with another individual.", "\"The person is being assessed for any injuries and the second person is assisting police with our enquiries.\"", "Police also deployed a helicopter, which had been circling overhead of the Auckland suburb.", "Photos show armed police going in and out of different properties, with a man speaking to police in handcuffs.\u00a0\u00a0"]
